'''支持联盟框架'''（{{lang|en|Advocacy Coalition Framework}}），为一种现行[[美国|美国]]、[[欧洲|欧洲]]的流行[[公共政策|公共政策]]模型。其特别强调公共政策的参与性，并在系统下分布次系统（{{lang|en|subsystem}}），以确定其政策的运行过程的稳定性以及可预期性<ref>{{cite journal | language = en | author = Peter John | title = Is There Life After Policy Streams, Advocacy Coalitions, and Punctuations: Using Evolutionary Theory to Explain Policy Change? | url =  | journal = The Policy Studies Journal | volume = 31 | issue = 4 | pages = 481-498 | year = 2003 | id =  }}</ref>。

== 简介 ==
在此系统的支持下，支持联盟框架可以集合所有的政策参与者到政策分析中<ref>{{cite journal | language = en | author = Edella Schlager  | title = Policy making and collective action: Defining coalitions within the advocacy coalition framework | url =https://archive.org/details/sim_policy-sciences_1995-05_28_2/page/n136| journal = Policy Sciences | volume = 28 | issue =  | pages = 243-270 | year = 1995 | id =  }}</ref>，
*分享政策运行哲学及理念；
*持续参与到高度的协同合作中。

